	Water: Cold damage is halved against you and your allies in the aura. If an enemy that has the water subtype ends its turn in the aura, that enemy is dazed until the end of its next turn. </specific>
		<specific name="Class"> ID_FMP_CLASS_128 </specific>
		<specific name="Level"> 22 </specific>
		<specific name="Power Type"> Utility </specific>
		<specific name="_ParentFeature"> ID_FMP_CLASS_FEATURE_4431 </specific>
		<specific name="_Subclasses"> ID_FMP_CLASS_956 </specific>
With this spell, a powerful elementalist can suppress the strength of other elements in his or her vicinity. For example, a fire elementalist might choose to suppress elemental water, reducing cold damage and hindering water creatures that remain close by.
	</RulesElement>
	<!-- DSH -->
	<RulesElement name="Stormy Emotions" type="Power" internal-id="ID_FMP_POWER_16511" source="Dungeon Survival Handbook">
		<Category> ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_CLASS_POWER,ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_ATTACK,ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_ENCOUNTER,ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_ENCOUNTER_USAGE,ID_FMP_CLASS_128,ID_FMP_CATEGORY_31,ID_FMP_CATEGORY_1,ID_FMP_CATEGORY_25,ID_FMP_CATEGORY_11,ID_INTERNAL_CATEGORY_STANDARD_ACTION,3 </Category>
